HEADWORD: Detruncate
<hw>De*trun"cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Detruncated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Detruncating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>detruncatus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>detruncare</ets> to cut off; <ets>de</ets> +
<ets>truncare</ets> to maim, shorten, cut off. See
<er>Truncate</er>.]</ety> <def>To shorten by cutting; to cut off; to lop
off.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

